article.headline: Northern Illinois 49, Central Michigan 43
article.story: MOUNT PLEASANT, Mich. (AP) -- James Hughes scored 12 points and Mike McKinney added 11 to lead Northern Illinois to a 49-43 win over Central Michigan in a Mid-American Conference game Thursday night. The Chippewas (3-14, 1-8) held a 41-39 lead with 5:05 left as Sefton Barrett -- Central Michigan's leading scorer on the season -- scored from underneath the basket for his only points of the game. But the Huskies (10-7, 5-4) responded with a 9-0 run. Todd Peterson hit a 3-pointer down the stretch to give the Huskies a 4-point lead and Central Michigan turned the ball over twice in the final minute. Northern Illinois struggled in the first half, shooting 31 percent from the field in the half. The Huskies, who normally hit on 48.1 percent of their shots, connected on just 35.4 percent in the game. Eddie Spencer led the Chippewas with 12 points, while Justin Blevins scored 10 and Giordan Watson added 11.
